body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

What would you like added/supported?

> UDP table/endtable - I understand that Verilator is not ideal for Gate Level, definitely not for timing/SDF. But as a flow, say one wants to run pre-layout netlist sims, this feature is handy at times. 

Can you attach an example that runs on other simulators?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```verilog
primitive udp_mux2 (out, in0, in1, sel);
   output out;
   input  in0, in1, sel;

   table

// in0 in1 sel :  out
//
    1  ?  0 :  1 ;
    0  ?  0 :  0 ;
    ?  1  1 :  1 ;
    ?  0  1 :  0 ;
    0  0  x :  0 ;
    1  1  x :  1 ;

   endtable
endprimitive // udp_mux2
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

> Yes please
